TYPHUS & MALARIA - AFGHANISTAN
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Unidentified deaths - Afghanistan (Badakhshan): RFI 990217083037
Unidentified deaths - Afghanistan (Badakhshan) (02) today
Date: Thu, 18 Feb 1999
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Tajik Radio, Dushanbe, 17 Feb 99

Over 350 people aged between two and 70 years have died from the outbreak
of typhus and fever [Tajik: tablarza, which can also mean malaria in the
villages of (?Warfak, Zhumar), Nosay and (?Tangi Waruy) villages in Darvaz
District [eastern Badakhshan Province in the Islamic State of Afghanistan
in the past two weeks, the ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary of
the Islamic State of Afghanistan to Tajikistan, Sayed Ibrahim Hekmat, has
said in an interview with a Khovar [Tajik state news agency correspondent,
Muhammadato Sultonov.
Two days ago, 10 people from just one family died simultaneously as a
result of these diseases
--
